  "response": "Pyrex is generally quite durable, but it can break under certain conditions:\n\n1. Thermal shock: Sudden temperature changes can cause Pyrex to crack or shatter. For example, taking a dish from the freezer and putting it directly into a hot oven.\n\n2. Physical impact: While Pyrex is stronger than regular glass, it can still break if dropped or hit with significant force.\n\n3. Surface scratches: Deep scratches can weaken the glass and make it more prone to breaking.\n\n4. Manufacturing defects: Rare manufacturing flaws can make some pieces more susceptible to breaking.\n\nModern Pyrex is made of tempered glass, which is more resistant to breakage than older versions. However, it's still recommended to handle it carefully, avoid extreme temperature changes, and inspect for damage before use.",
